 No exceptions please!\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Hotel Accommodations: Crowne Plaza Chicago O’Hare Hotel &amp; Conference Center, Rosemont, IL</span>:</strong>\r\n5440 North River Road, Rosemont, IL 60018. <a href=\"http://www.crowneplazaohare.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.crowneplazaohare.com</a> Register by clicking the link:\r\n<a href=\"https://resweb.passkey.com/Resweb.do?mode=welcome_ei_new&amp;eventID=9943616\" target=\"_blank\">https://resweb.passkey.com/Resweb.do?mode=welcome_ei_new&amp;eventID=9943616</a></p>\r\n<p align=\"left\">Booking Code:NLF you will get a confirmation number upon completion of your reservation, or by calling 877-337-5793 or central reservations at 843-760-5839 (Toll Free). The negotiated room rate is $135.00 single or double occupancy. You must mention the “National Lawn &amp; Garden Show” Booking code: NLF to get the discounted room rate. Please ask the hotel about its reservation &amp; cancellation policies. Please call by May 31, 2013, 8 PM CST to guarantee the discounted rate. After this date please call 888-233-9534 and we will make every effort to secure the discount, however prevailing rates will apply and rates are as high as $220 per night. <strong>There are several events taking place in our timeframe at the Rosemont Convention Center so rooms will be scarce, please reserve early. </strong></p>\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Complimentary Hotel Shuttle Service to/from O’Hare Airport</span></strong>:\r\nThe hotel is 10 minutes from O’Hare airport. The Crowne Plaza O\'Hare provides a 24 hour complimentary airport shuttle to and from O’Hare International Airport. Crowne Plaza’s pickup location for domestic travelers in O\'Hare is at Door 2 of the Shuttle Bus Center. International travelers please use the courtesy phones in the baggage area to contact the hotel to schedule a pick-up. From Midway Airport use rental car or book with private limo or cab as no complimentary service is available.\r\n\r\nDiscount Car Rental rates: We have negotiated special rates with Thrifty Car Rental.  The special code is valid throughout the year and nationwide.  Use Corporate Discount Code 004M002073 at <a href=\"http://www.thrifty.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.thrifty.com</a> or call 1-800-THRIFTY (847-4389) (US &amp; Canada) or 1-918-669-2168 (outside US and Canada). Or go to <a href=\"http://www.thrifty.com/reservations/index.aspx?corpnum=004M002073\" target=\"_blank\">www.thrifty.com/reservations/index.aspx?corpnum=004M002073</a>\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Driving Directions</span></strong><strong>: </strong>\r\n<strong>From O’Hare Airport.</strong> Head East on I-190, for 2 miles to River Road. Turn right on River Road and proceed down to 5440 N. River Road, directly across from the convention center.\r\n<strong>From the East (Chicago).</strong> Take I90 West to 190 (O’Hare exit) continue 15 miles to River Road exit. Turn right on River Road and proceed to 5440 N. River Road directly across from the convention center.\r\n<strong>From the West (Rockford).</strong> Take I90 East to Chicago. Exit on Cumberland Road North. Go right on Cumberland, 2 blocks to 1st light (Higgins/Rt.72). Go left on Higgins and proceed 1 mile to River Road. Go left on River Road and proceed to 5440 N. River Road directly across from the Convention Center.\r\n<strong>From the South (Indiana).</strong> Take 294 North (Wisconsin) and follow signs to 190 (O’Hare exit). Take 190 to River Road (1st light). Go right on River Road and proceed to 5440 N. River Road directly across from the Convention Center.\r\n<strong>From the North (Wisconsin).</strong> Take 294 South to 190 East, follow signs to O’Hare. Pay at toll. Stay in the right lane. Exit Mannheim Road South. Get back on the highway and follow signs to Chicago. Exit River Road South. Turn Right. Hotel is on the right side, approximately 2 blocks down.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Opening Reception</span>:</strong>\r\nPlease note that all participants are expected to be at the Hotel on Monday, June 10th, at 6:00 PM for Dinner Reception and Orientation Meeting.\r\n\r\n<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Emergency Contact:</span></strong>\r\nAppointments will begin at 8:30 AM on Tuesday, June 11th, and will conclude on Thursday June 13th at 11:30 AM. Please fax emergency contact information to 719-488-8168 in case we need to contact you during the event.\r\n\r\n</div>','NLGS Venue & Travel Info.','','inherit','open','open','','37-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:08:01','2013-08-08 13:08:01','',37,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=151',0,'revision','',0),(152,1,'2013-08-08 13:08:54','2013-08-08 13:08:54','','Overview Event History','','inherit','open','open','','history','','','2013-08-08 13:08:54','2013-08-08 13:08:54','',39,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/history.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(153,1,'2013-08-08 13:09:11','2013-08-08 13:09:11','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/history.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-152\" alt=\"Overview Event History\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/history.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Our sole mission since 1995 has been to provide an affordable, efficient, alternative to traditional\r\ntradeshows which assures buyer/vendor introductions in preset scheduled appointments.</em>\r\n\r\nIn 1988 NLGS founder and owner Bob Mikulas manufactured a Lawn &amp; Garden product for the retail market and on the advice of experts, hit the \"Tradeshow Circuit\". After attending approximately 20 booth style shows per year for many years he soon discovered that most vendors in the industry experienced a high level of frustration with ROI and measurable productivity at traditional booth style tradeshows. They just didn’ t get to meet the buyers they wanted to because it was uncertain if the buyers were at the event, and even more uncertain if they would stop at their booth.\r\n\r\nActing on research, which concluded that the biggest successes were achieved when buyer and vendor meet face to face in pre-set scheduled appointments, the first National Lawn &amp; Garden Show was held in 1995. A large segment of the Lawn &amp; Garden industry embraced the totally new and unique approach to bringing buyers and vendors together in a more efficient, productive setting that promotes personal relationships and no-nonsense selling. Both the buyers and vendors gave the 1995 National Lawn &amp; Garden Show rave reviews and paved the way for aggressive growth.\r\n\r\n<strong>NLGS EXPERIMENTS WITH BOOTHS</strong>\r\n\r\nThe NLGS Booth Division was introduced in 2002 as a supplement to the appointment-based event as requested by our buyers and in response to industry changes. Our goal was to validate the effectiveness of integrating a traditional booth style show with prescheduled appointments and to bring options to NLGS buyers and vendors alike.\r\n\r\nWhile we proved our theory by adding value to NLGS by successfully integrating the appointments and booths, in 2006 we decided that NLGS should maintain primary focus on what sets us apart from other shows- the <strong>appointments</strong>. Therefore in 2006, NLGS abandoned the booth division and returned to what we do best, put buyers and vendors together in pre-set scheduled appointments. We found there was little control over what occurs in a typical tradeshow setting, most importantly which buyers would actually attend. Registrations for typical tradeshows would be high, but turnout low, and the uncertainty had too much impact on the NLGS reputation for excellence. Buyers at typical tradeshows would get badges but often not show up, or they would not wear the correct badge so the exhibitors wouldn\'t be able to contact them. All of these uncertainties spurred the birth of NLGS in 1995.\r\n\r\n<strong>NLGS APPOINTMENTS</strong>\r\n\r\nNLGS is known in the Lawn &amp; Garden Industry for offering the most organized and productive model for conducting business. NLGS buyers must meet high volume buying requirements in order to participate in the event. Vendors pay a fee for guaranteed pre-set, scheduled appointments with buyers of their choice. The number of appointments available is determined by the number of buyers present and vendors participating, as allowed by the time and space available. Most vendors have 35-45 appointments over the course of the event, while buyers can see as many as their schedule allows.\r\n\r\n<strong>EVENT VENUE HISTORY:</strong>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"80px\"><strong>Year</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"200px\"><strong>Location</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"140px\"><strong>Venue Type</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1995</td>\r\n<td>Denver, Colorado</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1996</td>\r\n<td>Denver, Colorado</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1997</td>\r\n<td>Colorado Springs, Colorado</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1998</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Resort Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1999</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Resort Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2000</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Resort Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2001</td>\r\n<td>Dallas, Texas</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2002</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Convention Center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2003</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Convention Center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2004</td>\r\n<td>Denver, Colorado</td>\r\n<td>Convention Center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2005</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Convention Center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2006</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Convention Center</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2007</td>\r\n<td>Reno, Nevada</td>\r\n<td>Resort Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2008</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2009</td>\r\n<td>Atlanta, Georgia</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2010</td>\r\n<td>Colorado Springs, Colorado</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2011</td>\r\n<td>Chicago, Illinois</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2012</td>\r\n<td>Dallas-Frisco, Texas</td>\r\n<td>Hotel Venue</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nCurrently, the Lawn &amp; Garden Industry recognizes NLGS as the most exclusive and productive event in\r\nthe industry for Lawn &amp; Garden products. The event is known for bringing in the \"mid tier\" buyers who\r\ninclusively represent 90% of the merchandising opportunities in the US. Historically NLGS has had 14\r\nout of the top 20 Lawn &amp; Garden retailers in the US attend the annual NLGS event.','The History of the National Lawn & Garden Show','','inherit','open','open','','39-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:09:11','2013-08-08 13:09:11','',39,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=153',0,'revision','',0),(154,1,'2013-08-08 13:09:55','2013-08-08 13:09:55','','Buyers Why Attend','','inherit','open','open','','buyerwhyattend','','','2013-08-08 13:09:55','2013-08-08 13:09:55','',51,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BuyerWhyAttend.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(155,1,'2013-08-08 13:10:07','2013-08-08 13:10:07','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BuyerWhyAttend.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-154\" alt=\"Buyers Why Attend\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BuyerWhyAttend.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>As a Buyer...</em></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">This is Not Your Average Trade Show!</span></strong> The National Lawn &amp; Garden Show is not the trade show you\'re used to!</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>You save time with our signature pre-set appointment format.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>You select the products you want to see, eliminating unnecessary appointments.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Vendors bring the products to you at your private conference table.</strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Presentations will be personalized with your requirements. </strong></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Enjoy networking opportunities, events, product displays and new product prototype reviews, too!</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"/testimonials\">Click to see TESTIMONIALS</a>\r\n\r\nView our <a href=\"http://www.nlgshow.com/gallery\">Appointments photo gallery!</a>','Why Attend Buyers?','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:10:07','2013-08-08 13:10:07','',51,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=155',0,'revision','',0),(156,1,'2013-08-08 13:11:01','2013-08-08 13:11:01','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/O_pop.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-138\" alt=\"Overview Point of Purchase Showcase\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/O_pop.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe Point of Purchase \"POP\" Showcase gives buyers the opportunity to review vendor product displays, packaging and POP materials in a retail setting. Buyers have continuous unrestricted access to this area throughout the event in preparation for appointments and to revisit products of interest after their appointments have concluded.\r\n\r\nView our <a href=\"http://www.nlgshow.com/galleryEvents\">POP photo gallery!</a>','Buyer POP Showcase','','inherit','open','open','','56-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:11:01','2013-08-08 13:11:01','',56,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=156',0,'revision','',0),(157,1,'2013-08-08 13:12:03','2013-08-08 13:12:03','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/prototype.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-140\" alt=\"Overview New Product Review\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/prototype.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe New Product/Prototype area has the newest products to be introduced to the market and true product prototypes on display for buyer review. This secured area is available to buyers throughout the event. Here buyers evaluate products based on their uniqueness, packaging, price points and saleability in the market.','Buyer New Product/Prototype Review','','inherit','open','open','','59-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:12:03','2013-08-08 13:12:03','',59,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=157',0,'revision','',0),(158,1,'2013-08-08 13:12:57','2013-08-08 13:12:57','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/WhyAttend.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-132\" alt=\"Why Attend the National Lawn &amp; Garden Show?\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/WhyAttend.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe National Lawn &amp; Garden Show is offering a new service for first time\r\nparticipants! We want to make sure your goals and objectives are met and\r\nhelp you save time by being properly prepared. Whether you are a first time\r\nAttendee or Vendor, the NLGS will link you up with a seasoned \"veteran\"\r\nwho has attended this event at least three times in the past.\r\n\r\nYou will be able to contact this person prior to the event to discuss:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How to best prepare for your appointments</li>\r\n	<li>What to bring</li>\r\n	<li>What questions to ask during your appointments</li>\r\n	<li>How to get the most out of the event</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFirst time participants will also have an orientation meeting on, Monday\r\nJune 11, 2012 at 6:00pm where any additional questions can be answered\r\nby the event management. This service is yours simply by asking and is\r\ncomplimentary!\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">For mentors contact us at 888-316-0226 or 719-488-0226 or you may\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nlgshow.com/contact\">email us</a> to get paired up with a mentor\r\nspecifically for you.</p>','Buyer Mentor Program','','inherit','open','open','','62-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:12:57','2013-08-08 13:12:57','',62,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=158',0,'revision','',0),(159,1,'2013-08-08 13:13:55','2013-08-08 13:13:55','','Buyers VIA','','inherit','open','open','','buyervia','','','2013-08-08 13:13:55','2013-08-08 13:13:55','',64,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BuyerVIA.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(160,1,'2013-08-08 13:14:05','2013-08-08 13:14:05','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BuyerVIA.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-159\" alt=\"Buyers VIA\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/BuyerVIA.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe VIA event is a great way to relax and enjoy time with a select group of vendors in a relaxed social atmosphere. VIA events are generally held off site in a unique setting or location with dinner and cocktails throughout the evening. NO selling takes place at this function and is purely social in nature. We encourage all registered buyers to attend VIA events. This is a great way to further develop business relationships with current or new companies you are considering doing business with. See you at this years VIA event!!!!\r\n\r\nView our <a href=\"http://www.nlgshow.com/galleryVIA\">VIA photo gallery!</a>','Buyer VIA','','inherit','open','open','','64-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:14:05','2013-08-08 13:14:05','',64,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=160',0,'revision','',0),(161,1,'2013-08-08 13:52:14','2013-08-08 13:52:14','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/WhyAttend.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-132\" alt=\"Why Attend the National Lawn &amp; Garden Show?\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/WhyAttend.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>As a vendor...</em></h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">An Event with Guaranteed Results!</span></strong>\r\nThe National Lawn &amp; Garden Show is best described as \"speed-dating for Lawn and Garden products!\"</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>There\'s <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">no booth</span></strong> and <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">no additional set up expenses.</span></strong></li>\r\n	<li>Here, <strong>you are in the drivers seat</strong>. Instead of standing in a booth, you move from buyer to buyer according to a guaranteed, pre-set appointment schedule.</li>\r\n	<li>No more waiting and wondering if you\'ll see the right buyer. As a Vendor at the National Lawn &amp; Garden Show, you\'ll meet one on one with real decision makers who will give you a yes or a no on the spot! <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"/satisfactionguarantee\">Your satisfaction is guaranteed.</a></span></strong></li>\r\n	<li>We are so confident in the appointment format, that we guarantee you will meet buyers on a pre-set, one-on-one, appointment basis. <strong>No other trade event in the industry can offer you this!</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"/testimonials\">Click to see TESTIMONIALS</a>\r\n\r\nView our <a href=\"http://www.nlgshow.com/gallery\">Appointments photo gallery!</a>','Vendors Why Attend','','inherit','open','open','','86-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:52:14','2013-08-08 13:52:14','',86,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=161',0,'revision','',0),(162,1,'2013-08-08 13:52:54','2013-08-08 13:52:54','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/O_pop.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-138\" alt=\"Overview Point of Purchase Showcase\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/O_pop.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe Point of Purchase \"POP\" Showcase gives vendors the chance to display products, packaging and POP material in a retail setting. No \"pop-ups\" or traditional trade show backdrops are allowed. No utilities are available in this area. Buyers spend time reviewing products in the Point of Purchase Showcase in preparation for appointments and throughout the event.\r\n\r\nHow are products displayed in the Point of Purchase Showcase?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Up to three 2\' x 2\' POP tabletop or floor spaces can be reserved for each company, additional space may be purchased based on availability.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHow much does A Point of Purchase Display cost?\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Three spaces are included with vendor registration. This area measures 2\' deep X 6\' long and is either tabletop or floor space. Additional POP space can be purchased for $100 per 2\'x2\' space.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nView our <a href=\"http://www.nlgshow.com/galleryEvents\">POP photo gallery!</a>','Vendors POP Showcase','','inherit','open','open','','90-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:52:54','2013-08-08 13:52:54','',90,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=162',0,'revision','',0),(164,1,'2013-08-08 13:53:49','2013-08-08 13:53:49','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/prototype.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-140\" alt=\"Overview New Product Review\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/prototype.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Enjoy the rare opportunity to have buyers preview and evaluate your newest products in the event\'s secure Prototype Room. </em>\r\n\r\nBuyers provide written feedback on products in this area which gives you an invaluable source of information that helps shape the future design and production of lawn &amp; garden products. Buyers provide written feedback such as product uniqueness, pricing, packaging, etc. Vendors will receive the buyer\'s written feedback at the conclusion of the event. This secured area is accessible throughout the event for buyers only.\r\n\r\nSet-up is identical to the Point of Purchase (POP) area, either tabletop or floor display.\r\n\r\n<strong>How much does it cost to display in the New Product Preview?</strong>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style: none;\">\r\n	<li>1 Product Entry: $250</li>\r\n	<li>2 Product Entries: $350</li>\r\n	<li>3 Product Entries $450</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAdditional entries contact event management.','Vendor New Product/Prototype Review','','inherit','open','open','','92-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:53:49','2013-08-08 13:53:49','',92,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=164',0,'revision','',0),(165,1,'2013-08-08 13:54:31','2013-08-08 13:54:31','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/prototype.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-140\" alt=\"Overview New Product Review\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/prototype.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<em>Enjoy the rare opportunity to have buyers preview and evaluate your newest products in the event\'s secure Prototype Room. </em>\r\n\r\nBuyers provide written feedback on products in this area which gives you an invaluable source of information that helps shape the future design and production of lawn &amp; garden products. Buyers provide written feedback such as product uniqueness, pricing, packaging, etc. Vendors will receive the buyer\'s written feedback at the conclusion of the event. This secured area is accessible throughout the event for buyers only.\r\n\r\nSet-up is identical to the Point of Purchase (POP) area, either tabletop or floor display.\r\n\r\n<strong>How much does it cost to display in the New Product Preview?</strong>\r\n<ul style=\"list-style: none;\">\r\n	<li>1 Product Entry: $250</li>\r\n	<li>2 Product Entries: $350</li>\r\n	<li>3 Product Entries $450</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAdditional entries contact event management.','New Product/Prototype Review','','inherit','open','open','','92-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:54:31','2013-08-08 13:54:31','',92,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=165',0,'revision','',0),(166,1,'2013-08-08 13:55:32','2013-08-08 13:55:32','','Vendor Mentoring','','inherit','open','open','','v_mentor','','','2013-08-08 13:55:32','2013-08-08 13:55:32','',94,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v_mentor.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(167,1,'2013-08-08 13:55:44','2013-08-08 13:55:44','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v_mentor.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-166\" alt=\"Vendor Mentoring\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v_mentor.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe National Lawn &amp; Garden Show is offering a new service for first time\r\nparticipants! We want to make sure your goals and objectives are met and\r\nhelp you save time by being properly prepared. Whether you are a first time\r\nAttendee or Vendor, the NLGS will link you up with a seasoned \"veteran\"\r\nwho has attended this event at least three times in the past.\r\n\r\nYou will be able to contact this person prior to the event to discuss:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>How to best prepare for your appointments</li>\r\n	<li>What to bring</li>\r\n	<li>What questions to ask during your appointments</li>\r\n	<li>How to get the most out of the event</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFirst time participants will also have an orientation meeting on, Monday\r\nJune 11, 2012 at 6:00pm where any additional questions can be answered\r\nby the event management. This service is yours simply by asking and is\r\ncomplimentary!\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">For mentors contact us at 888-316-0226 or 719-488-0226 or you may\r\nemail us at <a href=\"mailto:moreinfo@nlgshow.com\">moreinfo@nlgshow.com</a> to get paired up with a mentor\r\nspecifically for you.</p>','NLGS Mentor Program','','inherit','open','open','','94-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:55:44','2013-08-08 13:55:44','',94,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=167',0,'revision','',0),(168,1,'2013-08-08 13:56:44','2013-08-08 13:56:44','','Vendors VIA','','inherit','open','open','','v_via','','','2013-08-08 13:56:44','2013-08-08 13:56:44','',101,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v_via.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(169,1,'2013-08-08 13:56:57','2013-08-08 13:56:57','<a href=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v_via.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-168\" alt=\"Vendors VIA\" src=\"http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v_via.png\" width=\"508\" height=\"221\" /></a>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Building a personal relationship between buyers and vendors is key to a healthy\r\nbusiness relationship. Vendors In Action (VIA) is made up of an exclusive group\r\nof vendors who see the importance of socializing in a relaxing environment with\r\nqualified buyers.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The VIA Party along with increased company exposure through complimentary\r\nVIA advertising in the directory makes VIA a smart choice for any exhibitor.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">What does a VIA Sponsorship Include?</h2>\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Exclusive Party</strong></h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Popular Vendors In Action (VIA) Party Night events offer exclusive\r\nopportunity for VIA sponsors to spend quality time with buyers in a\r\nrelaxing and fun social setting. Past events (pictured right) have included\r\noutings to <strong>Wrigley Field</strong>, a dinner party overlooking <strong>Lake Tahoe</strong>, and a\r\ntour and dinner at the <strong>Garden of the Gods</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>VIA Sneak Preview</strong></h4>\r\nBuyers take a sneak preview of the products displayed in the Point\r\nof Purchase (POP) showcase. The Sneak Preview takes place after\r\nthe opening reception and is only open to buyers and exclusive VIA\r\nSponsors.\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>NLGS Directory Ad</strong></h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>All VIA sponsors receive a full-page black and white</li>\r\n	<li>ad in the event Directory. Ads must be camera ready and meet<script type=\"text/javascript\">// <![CDATA[\r\n// Popup window code\r\nfunction newPopup(url) {\r\n	popupWindow = window.open(\r\n		url,\'popUpWindow\',\'height=700,width=900,left=10,top=10,resizable=yes,scrollbars=yes,toolbar=yes,menubar=no,location=no,directories=no,status=yes\')\r\n}\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n<a href=\"JavaScript:newPopup(\'/sites/all/themes/NLGS2010/images/content/adspces.html\');\">specifications</a>\r\n\r\nset by NLGS.</li>\r\n	<li>Sponsoring vendors also have access to the Point of Purchase (POP)\r\narea during special buyer viewing times throughout the event. Be where\r\nyour competition is not!!!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\">How much is a VIA Sponsorship?</h2>\r\nThe cost is $750.00 which includes access to VIA functions for up to three (3) attendees, a full-\r\npage black &amp; white ad in the Event Directory and a broadcast email promotion to the entire NLGS\r\n\r\n<a href=\"/sponsorship\">Other Sponsorship Opportunities</a>\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/sites/all/themes/NLGS2010/images/content/v_via.png\" />\r\n\r\nView our <a href=\"http://www.nlgshow.com/galleryVIA\">VIA photo gallery!</a>','VIA - Vendors In Action','','inherit','open','open','','101-revision-v1','','','2013-08-08 13:56:57','2013-08-08 13:56:57','',101,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/?p=169',0,'revision','',0),(170,1,'2013-08-08 13:58:08','2013-08-08 13:58:08','','Vendor Satisfaction','','inherit','open','open','','v_satisfaction','','','2013-08-08 13:58:08','2013-08-08 13:58:08','',103,'http://wordpress.nlgshow.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/v_satisfaction.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(171,1,'201